cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on developing a new cell association scheme in heterogeneous networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) to model the performance of the proposed cell association scheme, which is a concept commonly used in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for cell association in heterogeneous networks, which can be considered a systems and control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of the proposed cell association scheme on the average ergodic MU data rate, which is a key metric for multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses probability distributions to model the data rate ratio and traffic load ratio, which can be considered a game theory problem.
